    {
      "id": "8ab34e85bc277b6e0f58dec2b2b1a16d52fd3291",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 1,
        "name": "Robert Read",
        "email": "robert.read@intel.com",
        "username": "rread",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-08-23 00:10:35.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 5: (2 inline comments)\n\nThis features assumes that auster is always running the tests in TESTGROUP order, which is true today of course, but it would be nice to have the flexibility to reorder tests in the future (or run them in parallel, etc).  \n\nHowever, I also think that any significant change that that to auster would probably require a rewrite, and probably in a different language. So this is probably a ok hack for now. \n\nThis needs to be resubmitted, anyway, so no score for now.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 5
    },
